Gold Futures Increase for Sixth Day After Rising on Haven Demand

-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 
2011-02-20T23:11:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/gold-futures-increase-on-haven-demand-as-protests-flare-across-middle-east.html
Gold futures in  New York  gained for
a sixth day after mounting unrest in the Middle East last week
spurred demand for precious metals as a haven.  The April-delivery contract gained 0.2 percent to $1,390.90
an ounce at 10:08 a.m.  Melbourne  time. Bullion for immediate
delivery advanced 0.1 percent to $1,390.73 an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Pugh in Melbourne at 
 wpugh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
